<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-07-29T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-07-29T00:00:00-05:00" n="688" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d688">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 365.117/113.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                Ambassador <persName type="to">Page</persName></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 188.]</seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-07-29">
                                    <hi rend="italic">July 29, 1915</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: With reference to your telegram No. 332
                            of June 18, 1915, concerning the detention of Enrico Ajello for military
                            service, the Department sends you herewith copy of a letter<note n="5" xml:id="d688fn5">Not printed.</note> of July 14, 1915, from Mr.
                            Elmer C. Miller, asking that representations be made to the Italian
                            Government for the release of Mr. Ajello. It is desired that you request
                            an early decision of this case, and to report the result.</p>
                        <p>I am [etc.]</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Robert Lansing.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>